'''Issa Laye Lucas Jean Diop''' (born 9 January 1997) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for {{English football updater|Fulham}} club [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]]. Born in France, and a former France youth international, he plays for the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]].

Diop began his career at his hometown club [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]], making his senior debut during the [[2015–16 Ligue 1|2015–16 season]].<ref name=debut/> He became the club's captain in 2017, before leaving for [[Association football in England|English]] club West Ham United in 2018, signing for a club-record fee.<ref name=club-record-fee/>

==Club career==
===Toulouse===
Diop was born in [[Toulouse]], Haute-Garonne<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/FootballFicheJoueur58390.html |title=Issa Diop |newspaper=L'Équipe |location=Paris |access-date=16 June 2020 |language=fr}}</ref> and played youth football for [[Balma SC]] before moving to [[Toulouse FC]] in 2006.<ref name=FFF>{{Cite web |title=Issa Diop |publisher=French Football Federation |access-date=21 June 2018 |url=https://www.fff.fr/equipes-de-france/tous-les-joueurs/fiche-joueur/2543341590-issa-diop |language=fr}}</ref> He began training with the first team in September 2015, and signed a professional contract in November. He was part of an influx of young players to the squad that included [[Alban Lafont]], [[Zinédine Machach]], [[Alexis Blin]] and [[Yann Bodiger]].<ref name=gffn>{{Cite web |title=Issa Diop&nbsp;– West Ham are purchasing a future leader, but not a finished product |first=Adam |last=White |website=Get French Football News |date=18 June 2018 |access-date=21 June 2018 |url=http://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2018/feature-issa-diop-west-ham-are-purchasing-a-future-leader-but-not-a-finished-product/}}</ref>

He made his [[Ligue 1]] debut, aged 18, on 28 November 2015 against [[OGC Nice|Nice]], playing the full game alongside fellow debutant Lafont.<ref name=debut>{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/11/28/france/ligue-1/toulouse-fc/olympique-gymnaste-club-de-nice-cote-dazur/2046059/ |title=Toulouse vs. Nice – 28 November 2015 |website=Soccerway |access-date=25 June 2018}}</ref> He scored his first goal in his second appearance on 2 December 2015, contributing to his club's 3–0 win away to fellow relegation strugglers [[Troyes AC|Troyes]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Toulouse thrash Troyes in relegation six-pointer |url=http://www.ligue1.com/ligue1/article/toulouse-thrash-troyes-in-relegation-six-pointer.htm |access-date=6 December 2015 |publisher=Ligue de Football Professionnel |date=2 December 2015}}</ref> He made 21 appearances in his first season, helping the club to eight clean sheets. He was sent off twice during a season in which the club only avoided relegation with a win on the final day.<ref name=FourFourTwo>{{cite web |title=FourFourTwo's 59 Best Under-21 Wonderkids in the World: 40–31 |website=FourFourTwo |date=5 October 2016 |access-date=21 June 2018 |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/fourfourtwos-59-best-under-21-wonderkids-world-40-31}}</ref><ref name=footballlondon>{{cite web |title=Everything you need to know about West Ham's new centre-back Diop |last=Wilmot |first=Lee |website=football.london |date=21 June 2018 |access-date=21 June 2018 |url=https://www.football.london/west-ham-united-fc/transfer-news/issa-diop-transfer-west-ham-14780736}}</ref>

Diop made 30 Ligue 1 appearances in [[2016–17 Toulouse FC season|2016–17]].<ref name=Soccerway/> He was named captain of his local club for the first time in April 2017.<ref name=bbc>{{Cite news |title=Issa Diop: West Ham sign Toulouse defender for club record £22m |first=Simon |last=Stone |website=BBC Sport |date=19 June 2018 |access-date=15 June 2018 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44522330}}</ref>

The [[2017–18 Toulouse FC season|2017–18]] season saw Diop become club captain in October. Toulouse reached the quarter-finals of the [[Coupe de France]], but again struggled in the league, avoiding relegation after a play-off victory against [[AC Ajaccio]] in May 2018.<ref name=bbc/>

===West Ham United===
[[File:Hertha BSC vs. West Ham United 20190731 (180).jpg|thumb|upright|Diop playing for [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] in 2019]]

On 19 June 2018, [[Premier League]] club [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] confirmed the transfer of Diop, who signed a five-year contract. The fee, reported by British media as £22&nbsp;million, was not disclosed but was announced as a club record, beating the previous record of £20&nbsp;million set in July 2017 with the signing of [[Marko Arnautović]].<ref name=club-record-fee>{{cite web |title=West Ham sign sought-after French defender Issa Diop |publisher=West Ham United F.C. |date=19 June 2018 |access-date=19 June 2018 |url=https://www.whufc.com/news/articles/2018/june/19-june/west-ham-sign-sought-after-french-defender-issa-diop}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Issa Diop: West Ham sign Toulouse defender for club record £22m |first=Simon |last=Stone |website=BBC Sport |date=19 June 2018 |access-date=16 July 2018 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44522330}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=West Ham sign French defender Diop for club record fee |work=Reuters |date=19 June 2018 |access-date=20 June 2018 |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-soccer-england-whu-diop/west-ham-sign-french-defender-diop-for-club-record-fee-idUKKBN1JF2PN}}</ref> Diop made his Premier League and West Ham debut on 25 August. In a 3–1 away defeat by [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], he scored an own goal and in doing so became the first West Ham player to score an own goal on his debut in the Premier League.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/issa-diop-makes-premier-league-history-with-own-goal-against/m64yystw8wde1b4vyv54wvu1h |title=Issa Diop makes Premier League history with own goal against Arsenal |website=Goal (website) |first=Shina |last=Oludare |date=25 August 2018 |access-date=26 August 2018}}</ref> Three days later, Diop scored his first goal for the club, in an [[EFL Cup]] game against [[AFC Wimbledon]] after conceding a goal after only 72 seconds, Diop scored an equalising goal for West Ham who went on to win 3–1.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45254458 |title=AFC Wimbledon 1–3 West Ham United |date=28 August 2018 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=30 September 2018}}</ref> He won early season praise for his performances particularly against Arsenal and against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] whose manager, [[José Mourinho]] commended Diop's performance in West Ham's 3–1 win over his club and of the scout who had identified the potential of Diop.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.co.uk/football/blog-football-africa/story/3617310/issa-diops-class-shines-through-despite-chaotic-week |title=Issa Diop's class shines through despite chaotic week |first=Ed |last=Dove |publisher=ESPN |date=30 August 2018 |access-date=30 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/west-ham-man-united-jose-mourinho-monster-issa-diop-dominating-paul-pogba-midfield-a3949211.html |title=Jose Mourinho hails West Ham 'monster' Issa Diop for 'dominating' Paul Pogba and Manchester United |first=James |last=Robson |newspaper=Evening Standard |date=29 September 2018 |access-date=11 October 2018}}</ref> On 22 February 2019, Diop scored his first Premier League goal in a 3–1 home win against [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]].<ref>{{cite web |title=West Ham United 3–1 Fulham |first=Shamoon |last=Hafez |website=BBC Sport |date=22 February 2019 |access-date=17 June 2019 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44522330}}</ref>

On 22 September 2020, Diop was pulled from the West Ham squad before their [[EFL Cup]] game against [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]] after testing positive for [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=West Ham boss & two players have Covid-19|language=en-GB|work=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54258226|access-date=2020-09-23}}</ref> On 9 February 2021, in a [[FA Cup]] game against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]], Diop became the first [[Substitute (association football)#Concussion substitute|concussion substitute]] in English football when he was replaced by [[Ryan Fredericks]] following a head injury.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/55951207|title=Solskjaer praises Man Utd mentality|publisher=BBC}}</ref> The club subsequently reported that Diop had suffered no adverse effects,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whufc.com/news/articles/2021/february/12-february/west-ham-united-issue-issa-diop-and-angelo-ogbonna-update|title=West Ham United issue Issa Diop and Angelo Ogbonna update|access-date=13 February 2021|date=12 February 2021}}</ref> with manager [[David Moyes]] praising the club's medical staff for the way they handled Diop's injury.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/56042422|title=Issa Diop: David Moyes backs West Ham medical team for taking off defender|work=[[BBC Sport]]|access-date=13 February 2021|date=12 February 2021}}</ref> Although initially a regular player for West Ham, following the arrival of [[Craig Dawson]] and [[Kurt Zouma]] in the 2021–22 season, Diop was picked less often.<ref name="BBC Sport Transfer">{{cite web | title=Fulham sign West Ham defender Diop in £15m deal | website=BBC Sport | date=9 August 2022 | url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/62478215 | access-date=11 August 2022}}</ref> Before transferring to Fulham in August 2022, Diop made 121 appearances for West Ham scoring eight goals.<ref name=whuxfer/>

===Fulham===
On 10 August 2022, Diop transferred permanently to [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] on a five-year contract for an undisclosed fee.<ref name=whuxfer>{{cite web | title=Issa Diop joins Fulham | publisher=West Ham United | url=https://www.whufc.com/news/issa-diop-joins-fulham | date=10 August 2022 | access-date=10 August 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Diop signs for Fulham |url=https://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2022/august/10/issa-diop-signs-for-fulham/ |publisher=Fulham |access-date=10 August 2022 |date=10 August 2022 }}</ref> Diop made his Fulham debut on 23 August in a 2–0 away defeat to [[EFL League Two|League Two]] team, [[Crawley Town F.C.|Crawley Town]] in the [[EFL Cup|League Cup]] second round.<ref name="News and Star 2022">{{cite web | title=Formbook goes out the window as Crawley stun Fulham | website=News and Star | date=23 August 2022 | url=https://www.newsandstar.co.uk/sport/national/20721881.formbook-goes-window-crawley-stun-fulham/ | access-date=24 August 2022}}</ref> Diop scored his first goal for Fulham on 15 October in a 2–2 draw at home to [[AFC Bournemouth]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Fulham and Bournemouth fight out entertaining draw |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63182449 |access-date=2022-12-30}}</ref>

==International career==
Diop has been a [[France national youth football team|youth international]] for France at every level, making his first appearance for [[France national under-16 football team|France U16]] in 2013. He was part of the team that won the [[2016 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]], scoring in the final.<ref>{{cite web |title=Under-19 – France-Italy |publisher=UEFA |access-date=15 June 2018 |url=https://www.uefa.com/under19/match/2020326--france-vs-italy/}}</ref> In addition to winning the tournament itself, Diop was also named in the Team of the Tournament.<ref name="UEFA19" />

He made his debut for [[France national under-21 football team|France U21]] in a [[2017 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification Group 3|qualification game]] for the [[2017 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]], against [[Ukraine national under-21 football team|Ukraine]] on 2 September 2016.<ref name=Soccerway/>

He is also eligible to play for [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] through his mother and for [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]] through his father.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whufc.com/news/articles/2018/june/19-june/nine-things-you-need-know-about-new-signing-issa-diop |title=Nine things you need to know about new signing Issa Diop |publisher=West Ham United F.C. |access-date=20 June 2018}}</ref> In October 2018, he confirmed his international commitment to France.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45821890 |title=West Ham's Issa Diop confirms international future is with France |date=11 October 2018 |first=Danesius |last=Marteh |website=BBC Sport |access-date=11 October 2018}}</ref>

On 19 March 2026, it was announced that Diop had been selected to the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]] for the first time.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Issa-diop-appele-avec-le-maroc-pour-la-premiere-fois-ayyoub-bouaddi-toujours-indecis-ne-figure-pas-dans-la-liste/1660757?utm_campaign=facebook&utm_medium=photo&utm_source=Social%20media |title=Issa Diop appelé avec le Maroc pour la première fois, Ayyoub Bouaddi, toujours indécis, ne figure pas dans la liste |trans-title=Issa Diop has been called up to the Morocco squad for the first time; Ayyoub Bouaddi, who is still undecided, is not on the list |publisher=L'Équipe |language=fr |date=19 March 2026 |access-date=19 March 2026}}</ref> Seven days later, his request to switch allegiance to Morocco was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref name="FIFA-Change">{{Cite web|url=https://knowledge.fifa.com/change-of-association-platform|title=FIFA Change of Association Platform|accessdate=26 March 2026}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Diop, at {{convert|1.94|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}} in height, has been credited as being "a tremendous athlete, excellent in the air and quick across the ground" by football magazine ''[[FourFourTwo]]''.<ref name=FourFourTwo/> He has played mainly as a right-sided [[centre-back]].<ref name=gffn/> Along with the two red cards received in [[2015–16 Toulouse FC season|2015–16]], Diop amassed 25 yellow cards over the course of his three seasons at Toulouse.<ref name=footballlondon/>

==Personal life==
Diop's grandfather, [[Lybasse Diop]], played for [[FC Girondins de Bordeaux|Bordeaux]] and was the first Senegalese footballer in Ligue 1.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tfc.info/graine-de-pitchouns-issa-diop |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613184644/http://www.tfc.info/graine-de-pitchouns-issa-diop |title=Graine de Pitchouns – Issa Diop |date=26 June 2015 |archive-date=13 June 2018 |access-date=29 January 2019 |publisher=Toulouse FC}}</ref> He is also of Moroccan descent through his mother.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.20minutes.fr/sport/football/2219567-20180212-tfc-france-senegal-maroc-capitaine-issa-diop-embarras-choix-avenir-international |title=TFC: France, Sénégal, Maroc... Le capitaine Issa Diop a l'embarras du choix pour son avenir international |website=20 Minutes |date=12 February 2018 |access-date=11 October 2018}}</ref>

On 19 June 2023, according to ''[[La Dépêche du Midi]]'', Diop was taken into custody in [[Toulouse]] for death threats against his partner.<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 June 2023 |title=Issa Diop en garde à vue pour " menaces de mort " envers sa compagne |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Issa-diop-en-garde-a-vue-pour-menaces-de-mort-envers-sa-compagne/1403625 |access-date=19 June 2023 |website=[[L'Équipe]] |language=Fr}}</ref>

